                "type": "text",
                "text": "From the repo scan: Telegram support is probably not another model provider. The app already treats threads as first-class objects and backends as Codex/Grok execution providers, so Telegram should likely sit above that as an external interaction surface for existing/new threads.\n\nFirst decision: what role should Telegram play in v1?\n\n1. Remote control: Telegram lets you start, steer, approve, and monitor agent threads from mobile.\n2. Notifications only: Telegram only alerts you when a thread is blocked, completed, failed, or needs approval.\n3. Chat mirror: Telegram mirrors selected desktop threads as two-way conversations."
